**Analysis of the Main Target Image**

1. **Overall Layout / Structures**  
   There are **two separate structures** in the scene:

   - **Left “Vehicle”**  
     - Two large orange cylinders lying horizontally (the “wheels”).  
     - A flat green rectangular block bridging across the two wheels.  
     - A red rectangular block stacked on top of the green piece.  
     - A blue cube placed on top of the red block.

   - **Right “Arched Houses”**  
     - Bottom row of three red arches (all oriented with the arch opening facing front).  
     - On top of the left arch: a blue cube with an orange wedge “roof.”  
     - On top of the middle arch: two yellow half‐cylinders side by side.  
     - Behind the middle arch: two tall yellow rectangular blocks plus one tall green rectangular block in front of them (centered).  
     - On top of the right arch: a red rectangular block with an orange wedge “roof.”  
     - A short green rectangular block tucked behind each of the left and right arches (at about the same height as each arch).

2. **Block/Layer Count**  
   - **Left Vehicle:**  
     - Total of 5 blocks (2 wheels at the bottom, then 3 stacked above).  
     - Visually 4 “layers” if counted from bottom (wheels) to top (blue cube).  
   - **Right Arched Houses:**  
     - Base layer of 3 red arches.  
     - Second layer with the blue cube, red rectangular block, and two yellow half‐cylinders on top of the arches, plus the two short green blocks behind left and right arches.  
     - A tall green block plus two tall yellow blocks behind the center arch.  
     - Two orange wedge roofs (one atop the blue cube, one atop the red block).  
     - In total 14 blocks for the right structure.

**Selecting Required Blocks from Dictionary**

Below are the dictionary indices (in **bold**), the color/shape, and how many times each is used.  Note that orientation must match exactly as shown—no re‐orientations allowed.

• **#10** (Orange cylinder), used 2× for the vehicle “wheels.”  
• **#6** (Green rectangular prism, short), used 3× total:  
  – 1× bridging the wheels on the left vehicle,  
  – 2× behind the left and right arches on the right structure.  
• **#5** (Red rectangular prism), used 2× total:  
  – 1× stacked under the blue cube of the left vehicle,  
  – 1× on top of the right arch (forming the “house” body).  
• **#3** (Blue cube), used 2× total:  
  – 1× at the top of the left vehicle,  
  – 1× on top of the left arch in the right structure.  
• **#1** (Red arch, front‐opening), used 3× along the base of the right structure.  
• **#7** (Green rectangular prism, tall), used 1× behind the middle arch on the right structure.  
• **#9** (Yellow rectangular prism, tall), used 2× behind the middle arch (the two tall yellow columns).  
• **#11** (Yellow half‐cylinder), used 2× atop the middle arch.  
• **#16** (Orange wedge), used 2× total:  
  – 1× as a roof over the blue cube (left arch “house”),  
  – 1× as a roof over the red block (right arch “house”).

**Step-by-Step Assembly Instructions**

Use the following step order (you may of course combine steps in practice, but here each is listed separately):

{
  Step1: Move block with index 10  --(Place first orange cylinder wheel)  
  Step2: Move block with index 10  --(Place second orange cylinder wheel)  
  Step3: Move block with index 6   --(Bridge the wheels with a green rectangular block)  
  Step4: Move block with index 5   --(Stack the red block on top of the green)  
  Step5: Move block with index 3   --(Place the blue cube on top of the red block)  

  Step6: Move block with index 1   --(Place first red arch for right structure)  
  Step7: Move block with index 1   --(Place second red arch)  
  Step8: Move block with index 1   --(Place third red arch)  
  Step9: Move block with index 3   --(Put a blue cube on top of the left arch)  
  Step10: Move block with index 5  --(Put a red rectangular block on top of the right arch)  
  Step11: Move block with index 11 --(First yellow half‐cylinder, atop middle arch)  
  Step12: Move block with index 11 --(Second yellow half‐cylinder, next to the first)  
  Step13: Move block with index 6  --(Green rectangular prism behind left arch)  
  Step14: Move block with index 7  --(Tall green block behind middle arch)  
  Step15: Move block with index 6  --(Green rectangular prism behind right arch)  
  Step16: Move block with index 9  --(First tall yellow block behind middle arch)  
  Step17: Move block with index 9  --(Second tall yellow block behind middle arch)  
  Step18: Move block with index 16 --(Orange wedge roof above blue cube)  
  Step19: Move block with index 16 --(Orange wedge roof above red block)
}

Following these steps (without any re‐orientation of blocks beyond what is shown in the dictionary) replicates the target image exactly.
